@apffiner that can be true if its tooooo hot... I just have trouble feeling 
my fingers and even moving them when its really cold out so I think it 
makes it harder. idk thats just me

@3Camj I'd disagree. Harder climbs are sometimes not even possible if it's 
too hot, bcs of lack of friction. And it especially affects sandstone 
climbs.

@minieggg1 My first time sky diving the first chute failed. I didn't panic, 
wasn't scared at all till I was like 150 feet from the ground and got a bit 
freaked cuz I knew I didn't have a reserve left.

@minieggg1 Some have it, some don't. Ever since I was young I always wanted 
to climb EVERYTHING!.... and I wanted to fly. That isn't logical, yet I 
still feel it consistently and strongly. = )
